body:
## Problem statement

I am trying to get security definitions working with OAuth2 in the spec generation. However, it seems like either I'm using the scopes parameter wrong or it's not supported.

## Go specification

I tried the following things:

```go
// ...
//     SecurityDefinitions:
//     - oauth2:
//         type: oauth2
//         authorizationUrl: /oauth2/auth
//         tokenUrl: /oauth2/token
//         in: header
//         scopes:
//           bla: foo
//         flow: accessCode
// ...
// swagger:meta
package main
```

```go
// ...
//     SecurityDefinitions:
//     - oauth2:
//         type: oauth2
//         authorizationUrl: /oauth2/auth
//         tokenUrl: /oauth2/token
//         in: header
//         scopes:
//           bla: foo
//         flow: accessCode
// ...
// swagger:meta
package main
```

```go
// ...
//     SecurityDefinitions:
//     - oauth2:
//         type: oauth2
//         authorizationUrl: /oauth2/auth
//         tokenUrl: /oauth2/token
//         in: header
//         scopes:
//           - bla: foo
//         flow: accessCode
// ...
// swagger:meta
package main
```

The resulting swagger json is always the same:

```json
  "securityDefinitions": {
    "oauth2": {
      "type": "",
      "flow": "accessCode"
    },
    "scopes": {
      "type": "",
      "flow": "accessCode"
    }
  },
```

When removing the scope array, or replacing it with `scope: foobar`, it simply removes the scope key:

```json

  "securityDefinitions": {
    "oauth2": {
      "type": "oauth2",
      "in": "header",
      "flow": "accessCode",
      "authorizationUrl": "/oauth2/auth",
      "tokenUrl": "/oauth2/token"
    }
  },
```

## Environment
swagger version: latest master of goswagger (installed today)
go version: 1.8
OS: Win10
